test_auth.py — 11 tests
Checks that the API properly controls who is allowed in.
It verifies that test1 and test2 can log in with their correct passwords, 
and that anyone without credentials, with a wrong password, or with a made-up
username gets rejected with a 401. It also flags two endpoints 
(GET /integrations and POST /integrations) that appear to have no authentication protection at all
 — which is a bug.

test_contract.py — 26 tests
Checks that what the API actually returns matches what the API documentation (Swagger) 
says it should return. For example, if the spec says an integration response should have id,
name, tenant_id, and type fields, this test opens a real response and confirms all four 
fields are there with the right data types. It also flags the two places where the spec 
documentation is itself wrong.

test_crud.py — 37 tests
Checks that the basic operations of the API work correctly end to end — creating an integration, 
reading it back, updating it, and deleting it. Then does the same full cycle for assets.
It also tests edge cases like deleting something twice, creating an asset under an integration
that doesn't exist, and checking that duplicate asset names are rejected with a 409.

test_negative.py — 22 tests
Checks how the API behaves when given bad or malicious input. 
It sends broken JSON, missing required fields, SQL injection strings, XSS code, and 
extremely long values — and confirms the API returns a proper 4xx error every time 
instead of crashing with a 500. A 500 on bad input means the server is not handling errors safely.


test_tenant_segregation.py — 19 tests
Checks that test1 and test2 are completely isolated from each other's data. 
It creates an integration and asset as test1, then tries to read, update, and delete them 
as test2 — every one of those attempts should be blocked with a 403 or 404. If any of them succeed,
 that is a data breach — one tenant can see or modify another tenant's data.

 Run the tests:
 ```bash
 pytest tests/test_auth.py -v --html=reports/auth_report.html --self-contained-html
 pytest tests/test_contract.py -v --html=reports/contract_report.html --self-contained-html
 pytest tests/test_crud.py -v --html=reports/crud_report.html --self-contained-html
 pytest tests/test_tenant_segregation.py -v --html=reports/tenant_report.html --self-contained-html
 pytest tests/test_negative.py -v --html=reports/negative_report.html --self-contained-html
 ```

